            <h2>Conference proceeding inclusion process</h2>

            <p>
                The conference preceding inclusion process at Axiom Indexing involves a comprehensive evaluation to ensure the inclusion of reputable and academically significant conferences within the index. Axiom is committed to using conference proceedings in it citation index. By so doing, it allows the firm to uncover new theories emerging, find new solutions to problems and developing concepts that helps in research. The process typically includes the following steps:
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Submission of Conference Information:</h3>
                      Organizers or representatives of academic conferences submit comprehensive details about the event for potential inclusion in the index. This information includes the conference title, organizers, scope, objectives, location, dates, call for papers, keynote speakers, previous editions' details, and adherence to ethical standards.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Preliminary Assessment:</h3>
                        The submitted conference details undergo a preliminary assessment by the editorial team to ascertain alignment with the index's inclusion criteria. This initial review determines if the conference qualifies for further evaluation.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Evaluation of Conference Quality:</h3>
                        Qualified conferences undergo a thorough evaluation to assess their academic quality, relevance to the field, scholarly significance, the reputation of organizers, past editions' success, peer review process (if applicable), and adherence to ethical guidelines.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Expert Review and Decision-making:</h3>
                         Subject matter experts or reviewers within the field conduct an in-depth assessment of the conference based on predefined criteria. Their evaluations are then deliberated upon by the editorial board or review committee to decide on the conference's inclusion in the index.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h3> Notification and Feedback:</h3>
                        Organizers of the conferences receive notification of the decision, accompanied by feedback or recommendations if applicable. Transparent communication fosters understanding and encourages improvements if necessary.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <h3>Regular Review and Updates:</h3>
                         Included conferences are periodically reviewed to ensure they continue to meet the index's standards. This iterative process allows for the maintenance of a curated list of high-quality academic conferences.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
